HEADWORD: Kier
<hw>Kier</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Icel. <ets>ker</ets> a
tub.]</ety> <fld>(Bleaching)</fld> <def>A large tub or vat in which
goods are subjected to the action of hot lye or bleaching liquor; --
also called <altname>keeve</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

